Governor Gboyega Oyetola of Osun has stated that he does not have money to buy private jets for monarchs or hard currencies to splash around for citizens. He, however, stated that he had been blessed with the capacity to transform the state through good governance He also stated that Osun state was “too sophisticated for kindergarten politicians to govern. It is costly to allow such people to experiment with Osun.” A statement issued on Thursday by his Chief Press Secretary, Ismail Omipidan said, the governor said this at the Palace of the Ooni of Ife, Oba Enitan Adeyeye Ogunwusi, during the flag-off of his re-election campaign in Ile-Ife. Also Read: BREAKING: Court Declares Adeleke As Authentic PDP Candidate In Osun He stated that Osun was too sophisticated to be governed by kindergarten politicians seeking to experiment with Osun. He added that he is a believer in the fact that politics is not a do-or-die affair and that he is not interested in fire-for-fire approach espoused by a certain governorship aspirant